{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-20",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_20_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 20 - If They Hang You",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 7,
  "page_start_sec": 251.52,
  "page_end_sec": 495.22,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.648,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 251.52,
      "end": 252.38,
      "text": "Right.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 252.9,
      "end": 255.34,
      "text": "Now you and Thursby are in Hong Kong with the bird."
    },
    {
      "start": 256.18,
      "end": 256.74,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 257.4,
      "end": 257.9,
      "text": "And then...",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 258.06,
      "end": 259.74,
      "text": "I didn't know him very well."
    },
    {
      "start": 260.04,
      "end": 261.76,
      "text": "I didn't know whether I could trust him."
    },
    {
      "start": 262.18,
      "end": 264.032,
      "text": "I thought it would be safest..."
    },
    {
      "start": 264.3,
      "end": 264.68,
      "text": "Anyway,"
    },
    {
      "start": 264.84,
      "end": 266.38,
      "text": "I met Captain Jacoby,"
    },
    {
      "start": 266.52,
      "end": 268.36,
      "text": "and I knew his boat was coming here,"
    },
    {
      "start": 268.72,
      "end": 270.9,
      "text": "so I asked him to bring a package for me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 271.03,
      "end": 272.26,
      "text": "and that was the Falcon."
    },
    {
      "start": 272.78,
      "end": 275.0,
      "text": "I wasn't sure I could trust Floyd,"
    },
    {
      "start": 275.42,
      "end": 277.02,
      "text": "and that was safer than running the"
    },
    {
      "start": 277.02,
      "end": 278.66,
      "text": "risk of having it where he could get it."
    },
    {
      "start": 279.8,
      "end": 280.2,
      "text": "All right,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 280.36,
      "end": 283.04,
      "text": "then you and Thursby caught one of the fast boats over."
    },
    {
      "start": 283.72,
      "end": 284.06,
      "text": "Then what?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 285.408,
      "end": 287.22,
      "text": "Then I was afraid of Gutman.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 288.06,
      "end": 289.08,
      "text": "I knew he had people,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 289.24,
      "end": 290.3,
      "text": "connections everywhere,"
    },
    {
      "start": 290.66,
      "end": 291.54,
      "text": "and he'd soon"
    },
    {
      "start": 291.64,
      "end": 292.56,
      "text": "know what we had done."
    },
    {
      "start": 293.3,
      "end": 296.3,
      "text": "And I was afraid he'd have learned that we had left Hong Kong for San",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 296.44,
      "end": 296.82,
      "text": "Francisco."
    },
    {
      "start": 298.06,
      "end": 299.42,
      "text": "He was in New York,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 299.52,
      "end": 301.6,
      "text": "and I knew if he heard that by cable,"
    },
    {
      "start": 301.7,
      "end": 303.32,
      "text": "even some time after we'd"
    },
    {
      "start": 303.42,
      "end": 303.58,
      "text": "left,"
    },
    {
      "start": 304.06,
      "end": 305.66,
      "text": "he could get here by the time we did."
    },
    {
      "start": 305.92,
      "end": 306.88,
      "text": "And he did."
    },
    {
      "start": 307.94,
      "end": 308.94,
      "text": "I didn't know that then,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 309.08,
      "end": 309.94,
      "text": "but I was afraid"
    },
    {
      "start": 309.94,
      "end": 310.26,
      "text": "of it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 310.34,
      "end": 312.98,
      "text": "and I had to wait here until Captain Jacoby arrived."
    },
    {
      "start": 313.3,
      "end": 315.56,
      "text": "And I was afraid Gutman would find me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 315.72,
      "end": 317.6,
      "text": "or find Floyd and buy him over."
    },
    {
      "start": 318.63,
      "end": 320.18,
      "text": "That's why I came to you and Mr.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 320.26,
      "end": 321.88,
      "text": "Archer and asked you to watch him"
    },
    {
      "start": 322.08,
      "end": 324.38,
      "text": "for—' That's a lie,' Spade said."
    },
    {
      "start": 324.56,
      "end": 326.68,
      "text": "You had Thursby hooked and you knew it."
    },
    {
      "start": 326.96,
      "end": 328.6,
      "text": "He was a sucker for women."
    },
    {
      "start": 328.82,
      "end": 330.78,
      "text": "His record shows that."
    },
    {
      "start": 331.4,
      "end": 333.34,
      "text": "The only falls he ever took were over women."
    },
    {
      "start": 334.02,
      "end": 334.8,
      "text": "And once a chump,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 334.88,
      "end": 335.76,
      "text": "always a chump."
    },
    {
      "start": 336.66,
      "end": 337.94,
      "text": "Maybe you didn't know his record,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 338.08,
      "end": 339.7,
      "text": "but you'd know you'd had him safe."
    },
    {
      "start": 341.1,
      "end": 342.78,
      "text": "She blushed and looked timidly at him.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 343.44,
      "end": 343.92,
      "text": "He said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 344.9,
      "end": 346.56,
      "text": "You wanted to get him out of the way",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 346.56,
      "end": 348.34,
      "text": "before Jacobi arrived with the loot."
    },
    {
      "start": 349.04,
      "end": 349.76,
      "text": "What was your scheme?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 351.18,
      "end": 353.94,
      "text": "I knew he'd left the States with a gambler,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 354.0,
      "end": 354.86,
      "text": "after some trouble."
    },
    {
      "start": 356.1,
      "end": 357.22,
      "text": "I didn't know what it was,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 357.26,
      "end": 360.54,
      "text": "but I thought that if it was anything serious and he saw a detective"
    },
    {
      "start": 360.78,
      "end": 361.26,
      "text": "watching him,"
    },
    {
      "start": 361.42,
      "end": 363.24,
      "text": "he'd think it was on account of the old"
    },
    {
      "start": 363.24,
      "end": 365.36,
      "text": "trouble and would be frightened into going"
    },
    {
      "start": 365.54,
      "end": 365.8,
      "text": "away."
    },
    {
      "start": 366.74,
      "end": 367.648,
      "text": "I didn't think—'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 368.0,
      "end": 369.56,
      "text": "\"'You told him he was being shadowed,'"
    },
    {
      "start": 370.304,
      "end": 371.38,
      "text": "Spade said confidently.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 372.224,
      "end": 373.38,
      "text": "Miles hadn't many brains,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 373.74,
      "end": 376.38,
      "text": "but he wasn't clumsy enough to be spotted the first night."
    },
    {
      "start": 377.86,
      "end": 378.52,
      "text": "\"'I told him,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 378.56,
      "end": 379.0,
      "text": "yes."
    },
    {
      "start": 380.32,
      "end": 381.72,
      "text": "When we went for a walk that night,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 381.82,
      "end": 383.6,
      "text": "I pretended to discover Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 383.72,
      "end": 383.9,
      "text": "Archer"
    },
    {
      "start": 384.04,
      "end": 386.8,
      "text": "following us and pointed him out to Floyd.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 387.6,
      "end": 388.34,
      "text": "She sobbed.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 388.77,
      "end": 390.62,
      "text": "\"'But please believe me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 390.66,
      "end": 390.88,
      "text": "Sam,"
    },
    {
      "start": 391.08,
      "end": 394.08,
      "text": "that I wouldn't have done it if I thought Floyd would kill him."
    },
    {
      "start": 394.34,
      "end": 396.86,
      "text": "I thought he'd be frightened into leaving the city."
    },
    {
      "start": 397.08,
      "end": 398.84,
      "text": "I didn't for a minute think he'd"
    },
    {
      "start": 398.94,
      "end": 400.0,
      "text": "shoot him like that.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 401.408,
      "end": 403.46,
      "text": "Spade smiled wolfishly with his lips,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 403.52,
      "end": 405.1,
      "text": "but not at all with his eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 405.96,
      "end": 406.36,
      "text": "He said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 406.91,
      "end": 408.64,
      "text": "\"'If you thought he wouldn't,"
    },
    {
      "start": 408.66,
      "end": 409.696,
      "text": "you were right.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 410.78,
      "end": 412.24,
      "text": "The girl's upraised face held",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 412.44,
      "end": 413.24,
      "text": "utter astonishment."
    },
    {
      "start": 414.208,
      "end": 414.72,
      "text": "Spade said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 414.88,
      "end": 416.96,
      "text": "\"'Thursby didn't shoot him.'\""
    },
    {
      "start": 418.336,
      "end": 420.98,
      "text": "Incredulity joined the astonishment in the girl's face.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 422.016,
      "end": 422.56,
      "text": "Spade said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 423.488,
      "end": 424.64,
      "text": "\"'Miles hadn't many brains,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 424.7,
      "end": 424.92,
      "text": "but"
    },
    {
      "start": 425.5,
      "end": 427.36,
      "text": "he had had too many years' experience as"
    },
    {
      "start": 427.36,
      "end": 430.3,
      "text": "a detective to be caught like that by a man he was shadowing."
    },
    {
      "start": 430.61,
      "end": 431.5,
      "text": "Up a blind"
    },
    {
      "start": 431.64,
      "end": 431.88,
      "text": "alley,"
    },
    {
      "start": 432.02,
      "end": 433.58,
      "text": "with his gun tucked away on his hip?"
    },
    {
      "start": 434.272,
      "end": 434.86,
      "text": "Not a chance.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 435.27,
      "end": 436.74,
      "text": "He was as dumb"
    },
    {
      "start": 436.74,
      "end": 437.78,
      "text": "as any man ought to be,"
    },
    {
      "start": 437.92,
      "end": 439.14,
      "text": "but he wasn't that dumb."
    },
    {
      "start": 439.62,
      "end": 441.26,
      "text": "The only two ways out of"
    },
    {
      "start": 441.38,
      "end": 442.66,
      "text": "the alley could have been watched from"
    },
    {
      "start": 442.66,
      "end": 444.22,
      "text": "the edge of Bush Street over the tunnel."
    },
    {
      "start": 444.98,
      "end": 445.36,
      "text": "You'd",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 445.42,
      "end": 446.94,
      "text": "told us Thursby was a bad actor."
    },
    {
      "start": 447.42,
      "end": 449.98,
      "text": "He couldn't have tricked Miles into the alley like that,"
    },
    {
      "start": 450.12,
      "end": 451.66,
      "text": "and he couldn't have driven him in."
    },
    {
      "start": 452.06,
      "end": 453.12,
      "text": "He was dumb,"
    },
    {
      "start": 453.24,
      "end": 454.912,
      "text": "but not dumb enough for that.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 455.68,
      "end": 458.0,
      "text": "He ran his tongue across the inside of his",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 458.0,
      "end": 460.14,
      "text": "lips and smiled affectionately at the girl."
    },
    {
      "start": 460.32,
      "end": 461.1,
      "text": "He said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 462.304,
      "end": 463.88,
      "text": "\"'But he'd have gone up there with you,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 464.0,
      "end": 464.26,
      "text": "Angel,"
    },
    {
      "start": 464.42,
      "end": 466.38,
      "text": "if he was sure nobody else was up there."
    },
    {
      "start": 466.64,
      "end": 466.74,
      "text": "You"
    },
    {
      "start": 467.42,
      "end": 468.03,
      "text": "you were his client,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 468.28,
      "end": 471.08,
      "text": "so he would have had no reason for not dropping the"
    },
    {
      "start": 471.12,
      "end": 472.24,
      "text": "shadow on your say-so,"
    },
    {
      "start": 472.71,
      "end": 474.72,
      "text": "and if you had caught up with him and asked him to"
    },
    {
      "start": 474.72,
      "end": 476.14,
      "text": "go up there he'd have gone."
    },
    {
      "start": 476.61,
      "end": 478.46,
      "text": "He was just dumb enough for that."
    },
    {
      "start": 479.6,
      "end": 479.78,
      "text": "He'd have",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 479.86,
      "end": 482.24,
      "text": "licked his lips and looked you up and down and gone."
    },
    {
      "start": 483.04,
      "end": 484.04,
      "text": "And then you could",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 484.04,
      "end": 485.74,
      "text": "have stood as close to him as you liked"
    },
    {
      "start": 485.74,
      "end": 487.3,
      "text": "in the dark and put a hole through"
    },
    {
      "start": 487.3,
      "end": 489.97,
      "text": "him with the gun you had got from Thursby that evening.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 491.648,
      "end": 492.9,
      "text": "Brigitte O'Shaughnessy shrank back",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 492.9,
      "end": 494.52,
      "text": "from him until the edge of the table"
    },
    {
      "start": 494.72,
      "end": 495.22,
      "text": "stopped her."
    }
  ]
}